        <td bgcolor='dimgray' valign='top' width='100%'><font color='white' face='Verdana, Arial, Helvetica' size='2'>This is going to be the petition, I am going to address 2 issues.  Pet enhancements, and spell availability.  This is your final chance to suggest changes.  If I get anyone saying this is to overpowered after I post this to an online petition site this weekend, I will come over to your house and deleting your necro myself.  </P><P>Proposed Changes :</P><P>Spell availability:</P><P>We propose that the post 40 spells be moved to locations where Necromancers of the spell level can reach, with one group.  Also increase the drop rate so that the spells drop 75 percent of the time.  </P><P>Pets (w/ Encyclopedia Necrotheurgia):</P><P>Lvl 53 Pet - Lvl 40-44 / 1300-1450 HP<BR>Punch - unchanged<BR>Life tap (50)<BR>Backstab - unchanged<BR>Dual Wield/Attack<BR>AC 500<BR>10 percent lower than the masters</P><P>Lvl 56 Pet - Lvl 42-46 / 1600 - 1800 HP<BR>Punch - unchanged<BR>Lifetap (max 60)<BR>Dual Wield/Attack<BR>Flying Attack - Unchanged<BR>AC 600<BR>Same Resists as on the master</P><P>Lvl 59 Pet - Lvl 46-49 / 2800-3200 HP<BR>Punch (max 60)<BR>Lifetap (max 100)<BR>Dual Wield/Attack<BR>Bash (max 40)<BR>Kick (max 40)<BR>AC 800<BR>10 percent higher than the masters</P><P>Due to the 53 and 56 Necromancer pets being considered situational, we propose the addition of 3 new spells.  These spells will work much like the beastlord pets.  They will work only on the level 49, and only in indoor or raid type zones (All The Planes, Dragon Necropolis, Sleepers Tomb, West Wastes, Temple of Veeshan, Alkheva Ruins, Ssraeshza Temple, Sirens Grotto, Veeshan Peaks, Sebilis, Velketor's Labrynthe, Kael, Skyshrine, Thurgadin (both), Charasis, Chardok, The Hole, Grieg's End, The Deep, Acrylia Caverns, and Vex Thal) The stats should go as follows</P><P>Pawn of Thule (L54) <BR>Raises stats to the following<BR>Lvl 40-44 / 2400-2600 HP<BR>Punch (max 60)<BR>Life tap (50)<BR>Dual Wield/Attack<BR>Bash (max 30)<BR>Kick (max 30)<BR>AC 700<BR>Same Resist as the master<BR>12 point damage shield (ie banshee aura)</P><P>Squire of Thule (L57)<BR>Raises stats to the following<BR>Lvl 42-46 / 2600 - 2800 HP<BR>Punch (max 61)<BR>Lifetap (max 60)<BR>Dual Wield/Attack<BR>Bash (max 35)<BR>Kick (max 35)<BR>AC 800<BR>Same Resists as the master<BR>25 point Damage shield. (ungraded version of banshee aura)</P><P>Knight of Thule<BR>Raises stats to the following<BR>Lvl 46-49 / 2800-3200 HP<BR>Very toned down version of enraged at 20 percent health<BR>Punch (max 63)<BR>Lifetap (max 100)<BR>Dual Wield/Attack<BR>Bash (max 40)<BR>Kick (max 40)<BR>AC 900<BR>10 percent higher resists than the master<BR>32 point Damage Shield</P><P>On a side note, it would increase excitement in the game if these spells came with a different type of model.  For example, not only will it up the stats but change the pet to say a skeletal Drake for the 54 version, a Xin Thal (sp) for the 57 version, and a spectre with a particle effect for the 60 version.  </P><P>Also in an attempt to control pets more, we suggest the following (for all pet classes)</P><P>Pet Commands:</P><P>/pet hold - this is designed to counter act poor pathing and pet bugs. This should be in from level 1, and not an alternate advancement skill.</P><P>/pet heel - basically the same effect as above. Allows the casters to set a distance in which the pet can't go out of. This is designed to make moving in a dungeon with a pet safer. Just in case pet strays into an area of bad pathing, this will prevent him from getting more that a certain distance from the caster. This could be an alternate advancement skill, but I think it should be in from level one also.</P><P>Pet spells:</P><P>Renew Death (L50) - Heal pet for (L50) 500 points to (L60) 700 points.  </P><P><BR>Edited by - smaaug on 12/18/2001  23:41:37</P><P>Edited by - smaaug on 12/20/2001  23:07:25</P><P>Edited by - smaaug on 12/20/2001  23:16:38</font></td>
