        <TD bgcolor='dimgray' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana, Arial, Helvetica' size='2'>Removing the damage shields is an idea, but I think of it like this.  The pet buffs I designed to function equally in both groups and raids.  </P><P>When in raids, they arent going to taunt enough to gain agro, and if they do, they wont last long regardless.  So damage shields like banshee aura or barbshield arent going to matter.  What is going to matter is their resists and damage dealing</P><P>Now in groups where there is no warrior present, there is a good likely chance that they will gain agro, at least for a short time.  So this is where you need to have a good amount of hitpoints on the pet so they can last long enough for you to get off a pact, or the healer to heal them.  This barb shield is to give them a little more damage output.  A pet that is 10 levels lower than the group its hunting in, isnt going to do damage equivalent to that of the main tank, unless it adds a little everytime its hit.  Perhaps an idea would be to create a pet only version of banshee aura with a recast time.</P><P>As for zone requirements, I think the ones I posted will be the best bet, if you cut it down to zones that DMF doesnt work, you will only have like 4 zones.  That wouldnt make it very useful.</P><P>As for the group buffs spells, I like the idea.  You could lower the hitpoints, resists and AC if you could get group buffs spells to hold.  Perhaps some kind of bond between the master and the pet so that all the buffs that the master has, will also be applied to the pet.  This would also be an idea for resists, the resists of the master, equal the resists of the pet.  </P><P></P><P>Smaaug Darqsmoke<BR>Iksar Necromancer<BR>Brell Serilis</font></td>
